  "name": "Morrison COU2 — VAD hemolysis credibility assessment (Minimal profile)",
  "description": "Credibility assessment for CFD-based hemolysis prediction of the FDA generic centrifugal blood pump intended for ventricular assist device (VAD) use. The simulation model predicts absolute hemolysis index under pulsatile VAD operating conditions (flow rate 3–6 L/min, rotational speed 2400–3200 RPM) for a Class III implantable device. Model Risk Level 5 applies given the direct link between hemolysis prediction and patient safety decisions. Monte Carlo uncertainty quantification was performed across all 13 ASME V&V 40 credibility factors; seven factors were formally assessed and six were scoped as epistemic gaps. All assessed factors achieved required gradation levels under the Minimal credibility profile. Intended use scope: pre-market submission support for FDA 510(k)/PMA regulatory pathway, replacing bench hemolysis experiments under the specified operating envelope.",
  "bindsRequirement": "https://uofa.net/synth/req/vad-hemolysis-cfd-mrl5-req",
  "bindsClaim": "https://uofa.net/synth/claim/vad-hemolysis-cfd-absolute-prediction",
